# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Warframe Tracker — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values you need.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Google Drive Backup (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Enables the Google Drive Backup section on the Import / Export page.
# If this is not set, the feature is hidden and no Google scripts are loaded.
#
# HOW TO GET A CLIENT ID
# ──────────────────────
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/ and create a project (or use one you already have).
# 2. In the left menu: APIs & Services → Library → search "Google Drive API" → Enable it.
# 3. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client ID.
# 4. Application type: Web application.
# 5. Under "Authorized JavaScript origins" add the domain where you run the app,
#    e.g. http://localhost:5173 for local dev, or https://yourdomain.com for production.
#    (No redirect URIs are needed — this app uses the token model.)
# 6. Copy the Client ID below.
#
# NOTE: The Client ID is safe to commit / bundle — it is not a secret.
#       It identifies your app to Google but cannot be used without the OAuth
#       consent flow completing in the user's browser.
#
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
